sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant GW as OpenShift Gateway<br/>(data-science-gateway)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant WB as Workbench Container<br/>(JupyterLab/code-server/RStudio)<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3-compatible Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PyPI as PyPI / Package Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Git as Git Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,WB: Flow 1: User Accesses Workbench

    User->>GW: HTTPS/443<br/>OAuth/OIDC (OpenShift)
    GW->>RBAC: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS
    RBAC->>RBAC: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Kubernetes RBAC check
    RBAC->>WB: HTTP/8888<br/>plaintext (localhost/pod)<br/>Pre-authenticated
    WB-->>RBAC: Response
    RBAC-->>GW: Response
    GW-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: User Runtime Activities

    User->>GW: Notebook execution request
    GW->>RBAC: Forward
    RBAC->>WB: Forward
    WB->>S3: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS credentials<br/>Data access
    S3-->>WB: Data response
    WB->>K8s: HTTPS/6443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token<br/>oc CLI commands
    K8s-->>WB: API response
    WB->>PyPI: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>pip install (user-initiated)
    PyPI-->>WB: Package download
    WB->>Git: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>Token/SSH<br/>Git operations
    Git-->>WB: Repository data

    Note over User,S3: Flow 3: Pipeline Runtime Execution

    participant DSP as Data Science Pipelines<br/>Controller
    participant RT as Runtime Container<br/>(Elyra bootstrapper)

    DSP->>RT: Pod creation<br/>ServiceAccount
    RT->>S3: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS credentials<br/>Fetch pipeline artifacts
    S3-->>RT: Pipeline artifacts
    RT->>RT: Python package execution<br/>(local)

    Note over User,S3: Flow 4: Image Registration (Deployment)

    participant OP as RHOAI Operator
    participant IS as ImageStream API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Reg as registry.redhat.io<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    OP->>K8s: HTTPS/6443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount<br/>Apply Kustomize manifests
    K8s->>IS: Create/Update ImageStreams
    IS->>Reg: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>Pull secret<br/>Import images (SHA256 digest)
    Reg-->>IS: Container image layers
